<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Where buy/find components</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>You'll find <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/location/jewelry.htm">all jewelcraft vendor locations here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>All known vendor locations is here. If you don't find in this page the stone you are looking for, that means that your stone is not sold by NPC vendors. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Some stones are dropped only: black pearl, black sapphire, jacinth, diamond, blue diamond</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. You'll never see those stones by a merchant, except if a player sold them to this merchant <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>If you need one of those stone, you can buy it to another player (pay attention to auctions!) or go in a place where they drop. As far as I know, black pearl is dropped by Spectres (Oasis, Feerot), some giants (Rathe Mountain, SRo) and cyclops (Rathe Moutain, OoT).<br>Black saphire, diamond and blue diamond are dropped randomly on plane and in Sebilis, and sometimes on the Allizewsaur in OoT.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> At what level in the skill an item becomes trivial</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Here is a page where you can see all trivial caps for <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/jewelry/The_Art_of_Jewelcraft.htm#TrivialChart">all jewelcratf items</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br><br>You can notice that some items never become trivial (trivial&gt;250). And even on a trivial item a jeweler can fail. That depends on the jewelcraft skill (how much far from trivial level it is), lag in the zone (crafters relate that the lag decrease success rate), and the crafter's DEX (the higher the DEX is, the higher is the success rate). <p><table><tr><td><img src="http://www.ifrance.com/chimaera-res/Games/EQMryl/MrylSign04.jpg"></td><td><font color